{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-20233/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-20233"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["2:02:33"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["high"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A couple dances on an empty dancefloor covered in balloons and the remnants of a grand party."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-20233","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-20233"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1/aa2fe1b4-ed70-437c-ab7b-43ac5ac4f675","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:27:08.719Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In this dream sequence, Alma and Reynolds both appear as dark silhouettes against the colorful background of the party as Reynolds did during the earlier <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW247838565 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-14605.html\"><u>New Years Eve scene</u></a>. He is no longer singularly isolated from the festivities; it is the two of them, together, against the world. Alma is now dressed in a dark color, almost matching Reynolds’s suit, rather than in the contrasting pink dress she wore at the actual party. Their shadows seem to blend together, not fully clear where one person starts, and the next begins. They have become one.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:834.3391148325359,535.020933014354,155.11139354066972,316.70903110047834"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1/a49f3172-577c-4f2a-9d28-4076df00e99b","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:27:48.184Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The transition from Cyril gently moving the pram to Reynolds and Alma swaying on the dance floor links the (imagined) child to the (imagined) father. Alma takes care of Reynolds at times as if she is his mother, and he readily takes up this arrangement.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:801.107206937799,483.8038277511962,134.0849282296649,217.1411483253588"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1/2d3b230b-e958-4732-a49f-66e0c102b5d1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:28:07.318Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Alma’s vision returns to the New Year’s Eve party at Devonshire Hall. It likely does so as this was the site of a rupture in their relationship. Soon after, Alma hears Reynolds express regret about their marriage to Cyril. As “Auld Lang Syne” played in the background (mixed with Jonny Greenwood’s score), the couple “said goodbye” to one way of life and entered a new one. In this rewriting of that night, however, Reynolds and Alma dance peacefully and remain in love.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20233/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:50.694527511961525,43.16985645933009,270.7266746411483,164.05352870813402"}}}]}]}]}